rComments: Honestly the best professor and course at U of T. Packman is always there to help you if you are struggling with the course material. class is super interesting and not boring at all even though it is early in the morning ! I have never learnt so much about the music worldwide and it really opens up your thoughts about different countries.

rComments: Best professor at u of t. Classes are interesting and very interactive and never boring. Super helpful during class and office hours. Course material itself is super interesting if you have a music background already. Great course in general. Learnt so much about world music.

rComments: Entertaining! But could be a little dull occasionally.
One of the best profs I've had! Two years after taking this course, it still informs my work. I hope to take more from Packman; he's just amazing.

Outstanding professor. So passionate for great music. His course is in my top 3 of all time over 5 years at U of T. If you love music, make sure you find a way to have Packman as a professor. You will love him and the music he shares with you.

Good prof. Obviously passionate about what he teaches. Tests are easy to prepare for if you are willing to put in a little work and learn about the music. You will gain an incredible new perspective about music from him, even if you already love all sorts of music. The history and roots are very cool. He is a clear, gifted communicator.
Tests are fair. You won't get bored in his class, and he's very energetic. Girls, you will like him. :)
Very interesting prof. Specializes in Brazilian music and dance and therefore bases most of his lectures on this. Text is useless. Overall great prof.
